July 27, 1945
Germany

Dearest Folks

Well today was a big day for us We took the day off + went over to Rotenburg to teh Recreational center. We swam, played games + drank cokes, coffee + ate do-nuts. We played House [?] "H" Co. in baseball, "We have a league that was our last game from this Br. We won 7-5 today.

The news sure sounds good about Japan today it seems like I may not have to go over after all if they will hurry up + declare peace.

I am onnow [?] is a rouht day inspection I should have clean clothes + everthing but I don't. Iews [?] need a haircut.

Boy I'll bet y back will be burnin tomorrow. Write. 

Love always
O.L.